The G-1 League finals in China has been amazing to watch. The world champions iG were the first team to be eliminated, Alliance finished with a perfect 6-0 record and a number of new strategies were unleashed. As the dust settled and Alliance were declared the winners, taking the title from the Chinese in their own backyards, the results and gameplay seen fom the worlds best teams will no doubt have influence throught the Dota 2 community.

The Upsets

Whether due to the rumoured internal issues, a lack of tournament practice opportunities or their legacy of G-1 troubles come back to haunt them, but iG was not on form.
